client_messagetranslation.message:
Starting the Test Session:

  • Select the test(s) that need to be included in the session, then click the [Start Session] button.
  • Provide the Session ID to your students so that they can log in.

Approving Students:

  • Click the [Approvals (#)] button. The Approvals and Student Test Settings window will appear.
  • Click [See/Edit Details] for a student to view his or her accommodations and test settings and make any necessary changes (e.g., color background choice).
  • Click the [Approve] button for each student to allow entry into the session.
  • Click [Approve All Students] if all their settings are accurate and they can all enter the session.
  • To deny a student, click [Deny] and enter a brief reason (e.g., student selected the wrong test).

Note: Once students are approved, their settings for the current opportunity cannot be changed.


Student Lookup:

You can use this feature to look up student information if a student is having difficulty logging in.

  • Click the [Student Lookup] button in the top row.
  • Use the [Quick Search] tab to find a student using his or her MARSS/SSID number. Partial entries are not allowed.
  • Use the [Advanced Search] tab to find a student by district, school, and first or last name. Partial names are allowed. (e.g., entering "Fi" into the last name field will start a search for all students in the school whose last name begins with Fi).

Monitoring Student Progress:

Students who appear in the table below have entered this session. The page automatically refreshes every minute. When the page refreshes, the students’ statuses in the table below will update. The current status plus (#/#) will indicate how many questions have been answered by the student.


Stopping the Test Session:

  • When all students have completed testing or it is time for the session to end, click [Stop Session].
  • This will end the session, pause all your students' tests and then log them out of the online testing system.

Minnesota Assessments Secure Test Material

If you pause this test, the student will be logged out. If the student does not log back in within 45 minutes, he or she will be unable to see the questions that were already answered. Are you sure you want to pause this test?

Starting the Session:

  • Select the assessment(s) that need to be included in the session, then click the [Start Session] button.
  • Provide the Session ID to your students so that they can log in.

Approving Students:

  • Click the [Approvals (#)] button. The Approvals and Student Test Settings window will appear.
  • Click [See/Edit Details] for a student to view his or her accommodations and test settings and make any necessary changes (e.g., color background choice).
  • Click the [Approve] button for each student to allow entry into the session.
  • Click [Approve All Students] if all their settings are accurate and they can all enter the session.
  • To deny a student, click [Deny] and enter a brief reason (e.g., student selected the wrong assessment).

Note: Once students are approved, their settings for the current opportunity cannot be changed.

Student Lookup:

You can use this feature to look up student information if a student is having difficulty logging in.

  • Click the [Student Lookup] button in the top row.
  • Use the [Quick Lookup] tab to find a student using his or her SSID number. Partial SSIDs are not allowed.
  • Use the [Advanced Search] tab to find a student by complex area, school, and first or last name. Partial names are allowed. (e.g., entering "Fi" into the last name field will start a search for all students in the school whose last name begins with Fi).

Monitoring Student Progress:

Students that appear in the table below have entered this session. The page automatically refreshes every minute. When the page refreshes, the students’ statuses in the table below will update. The current status plus (#/#) will indicate how many test items have been presented to the student out of the total number of test items in the assessment. This does not mean that the student has answered all the questions so far. (For example, a student can be viewing a page that has 5 items, but not yet answered all the items on that page.)

Stopping the Test Session

  • When all students have completed testing or it is time for the session to end, click [Stop Session].
  • This will end the session, pause all your students' assessments and then log them out of the online testing system.

To print the requested content, click the [Print] button below. This will print the following pages: 1) cover sheet at the beginning and end of the printout that includes the student name and policies on security and privacy, 2) pages containing the requested test content. In addition, clicking the button closes this window.


It is important to adhere to the security and privacy policies for this procedure.

Delaware Secure Test Material

This printout contains secure test content and must be immediately and securely recycled on-site by authorized school staff.

Do not photocopy, enlarge, digitize, or retain printouts of test content. Such actions constitute a severe test security violation and must be reported to DEDOE.

In accordance with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), disclosure of personally identifiable information protected by privacy laws is prohibited. Please securely destroy all printed test content immediately after the end of this testing session.

This page allows you to access various system reports. They include:

  • Daily Number of Users Report—View how many TA and Student sessions occurred each hour in a day.
  • Server-side and Client-Side Latency Report—View data for both server and browser (client-side) latency times.
  • Blueprint Report—View content strand requirements for each test administration.
  • Abnormal Resumptions Report—View what type of browser and operating system combination was in use at the time of an "abnormal login."
